# expect: [1, 2, 3]
# Test: UFCS method call when parameter name shadows method name
# Previously caused runtime error: "expected Function or Closure, got Bool(true)"
# because xs.take(2) resolved "take" to the Bool parameter instead of stdlib.list.take.
takeOrDrop(take, n, xs) = if take then xs.take(n) else xs.drop(n)
main() = takeOrDrop(true, 3, [1, 2, 3, 4, 5])
